Perfkit is a service & web front end for composing queries and dashboards,
and sharing the results.

Platforms/Dependencies
=====================
Data Store:
* Google BigQuery              https://bigquery.cloud.google.com

Service:
* Google App Engine (Python)   https://developers.google.com/appengine/downloads
* Google API Client            https://developers.google.com/api-client-library/python/start/installation
* PyTest                       http://pytest.org/latest/getting-started.html
* WebTest                      http://webtest.pythonpaste.org/en/latest/
* WebApp2                      https://webapp-improved.appspot.com/tutorials/quickstart.nogae.html


Installation/Configuration
==========================
1. Create a new Cloud Console project.
2. Create client access tokens for your project, and add them to
   credentials.json.
3. Enable the BigQuery and AppEngine service for your project.
4. TODO: Create script/process for creating empty results table and test
   datasets.

Running Tests
=============
1. Install prerequisite libraries (noted above).
2. From a command-line and the root folder of your tests (common/py or
   explorer), run:
     py.test

   To run a specific class of tests, you can access the @pytest.mark.* values
   annotating the tests.  For example, to run all query-related tests:
     py.test -v -m query
